      "content": "Doubling up on your doses is a very risky idea, and you should never self-medicate in that manner. If your current inhaler isn't managing your symptoms, it means your asthma has changed, and simply using it more often won't fix the underlying issue. You need a doctor to assess if you need a different type of medication or a higher dosage, so please schedule that appointment.",
